BreadfundsUnit::initialize
├── when already initialized
│   └── it reverts
└── when not initialized
    ├── it sets the owner
    └── it prevents re-initialization

BreadfundsUnit::setTokenAllowed
├── when caller is not owner
│   └── it reverts
├── when token address is zero
│   └── it sets zero address allowed
├── when allowing a token
│   ├── it emits token allowed event
│   └── it marks token as allowed
└── when disallowing a token
    ├── it emits token disallowed event
    └── it marks token as disallowed

BreadfundsUnit::create
├── when token is not allowed
│   └── it reverts
├── when start time is zero
│   └── it reverts
├── when owner is zero address
│   └── it reverts
├── when initial deposit is zero
│   └── it reverts
├── when fixed deposit is zero
│   └── it reverts
├── when auto threshold is zero
│   └── it reverts
├── when minimum members is 0
│   └── it reverts
├── when minimum members is 1
│   └── it reverts
├── when maximum equals minimum
│   └── it succeeds (id 0)
├── when maximum is less than minimum
│   └── it reverts
├── when epoch duration is zero
│   └── it reverts
├── when small withdraws limit is zero
│   └── it reverts
├── when members array is empty
│   └── it succeeds with no members
├── when any member is zero address
│   └── it reverts
├── when members array contains duplicates
│   └── it succeeds and marks member present
├── when consensus threshold is zero
│   └── it succeeds (id 0)
├── when consensus threshold > 100
│   └── it succeeds (id 0)
├── when ratio is zero
│   └── it succeeds (id 0)
├── when ratio > 100
│   └── it succeeds (id 0)
└── when parameters are valid
    ├── it emits BreadfundCreated
    ├── it returns id 0 and increments nextId
    ├── it stores the breadfund
    └── it indexes members and reverse lookups

BreadfundsUnit::decommission
├── when breadfund is not decommissionable
│   └── it reverts
└── when breadfund is decommissionable
    ├── it transfers withdrawables to members
    ├── it deletes the stored struct
    └── it splits remaining balance equally

BreadfundsUnit::deposit
├── when breadfund does not exist
│   └── it reverts
├── when caller is not a member
│   └── it reverts
├── when deposit value is zero
│   └── it reverts
├── when before start time
│   └── it reverts
├── when at start time
│   └── it includes fixed and initial deposits
├── when already deposited in epoch
│   └── it reverts
├── when token transferFrom fails
│   └── it reverts
├── when making first deposit
│   ├── it records contribute and first-deposit flag
│   ├── it updates balances and withdrawable
│   └── it emits FundsDeposited and marks epoch deposit
├── when making subsequent deposits
│   ├── it keeps contribute unchanged
│   └── it adds to withdrawable by ratio
└── when ratio is zero
    ├── it accrues breadfund balance
    └── it keeps member withdrawable at zero

BreadfundsUnit::depositFor
├── when breadfund does not exist
│   └── it reverts
├── when target member is not a member
│   └── it reverts
├── when sender is not a member
│   └── it processes and marks first deposit for target
├── when deposit value is zero
│   └── it reverts
├── when before start time
│   └── it reverts
├── when target already deposited this epoch
│   └── it reverts
├── when transferFrom fails from sender
│   └── it reverts
└── when making first deposit for target
    ├── it records target contribution
    └── it marks first deposit true

BreadfundsUnit::withdraw
├── when breadfund does not exist
│   └── it reverts
├── when caller is not a member
│   └── it reverts
├── when days requested is zero
│   └── it counts as small withdraw with no transfer
├── when requested amount exceeds withdrawable
│   └── it reverts
├── when amount is below threshold
│   ├── it transfers to member
│   └── it reduces member withdrawable balance
└── when amount is above threshold
    ├── it creates a request and increments nextIdRequest
    └── it stores request owner and fund id

BreadfundsUnit::contest
└── when contested within window by a member
    └── it marks the request contested

BreadfundsUnit::executeContestedWithdrawal
├── when contest window still open and not contested
│   └── it does nothing (not executed)
├── when request contested and window passed
│   └── it does nothing (not executed)
└── when window passed and not contested
    └── it auto-executes and emits event

BreadfundsUnit::vote
└── when voting yes to exceed consensus
    └── it emits approval and executes the request

BreadfundsUnit::isTokenAllowed
├── when token mapping set to true
│   └── it returns true
├── when token mapping set to false
│   └── it returns false
├── when token not in mapping
│   └── it returns false
└── when zero address set to allowed
    └── it returns true

BreadfundsUnit::getBreadfund
├── when breadfund does not exist or is decommissioned
│   └── it reverts
└── when breadfund exists and is commissioned
    └── it returns stored breadfund

BreadfundsUnit::getBreadfunds
├── when ids array is empty
│   └── it returns empty array
└── when some ids do not exist
    └── it returns zeroed structs for missing ids

BreadfundsUnit::getMemberBreadfunds
├── when member has no breadfunds
│   └── it returns empty array
└── when member has breadfunds
    └── it returns the id

BreadfundsUnit::getMemberBalances
├── when breadfund does not exist
│   └── it reverts
└── when breadfund exists and is commissioned
    └── it returns members and zero balances

BreadfundsUnit::hasMemberDepositedInEpoch
├── when member deposited in epoch
│   └── it returns true
└── when unset or false
    └── it returns false

BreadfundsUnit::getCurrentEpochIndex
└── when checking time edge cases
    └── it returns correct indices (0,1,5)

BreadfundsUnit::isDecommissionable
├── when breadfund does not exist
│   └── it returns true
├── when breadfund owner is zero address
│   └── it returns true
└── when current epoch index is 0
    └── it returns false
